commit.message: Spleen 2.1.0 release.
Update ChangeLog prior to the 2.1.0 release.
Also fix latin small letter 'u' smoothing in the 32x64 CP437 version.
Mention that OTF versions should be used as last resort.
Mention OTB versions availability in the *BSD and Linux section.
Harmonize style for Cyrillic small letter 'Be' in the 16x32 version.
Harmonize styles for Cyrillic capital letters 'Sha' and 'Shcha'.
Harmonize styles for Cyrillic capital letter 'I' and short 'I'.
Fix Cyrillic small letters 'El' and 'Pe' smoothing in the 32x64 version.
Fix smoothing on more variants of 'u' in the 32x64 version.
Fix latin small letter 'u' smoothing in the 32x64 version.
Fix cyrillic small letter 'te' in the 16x32 version.
Harmonize cyrillic small letter 'de' in the 16x32 and 32x64 versions.
Fix thickness of the Cyrillic small letter 'Zhe' in the 16x32 version.
Fix Cyrillic capital 'Be' smoothing in the 16x32 and 32x64 versions.

Add base cyrillic (basic alphabet + most used extended) characters.

This adds basic cyrillic alphabet and some extended characters along
with combining breve and diaeresis characters.
Document how wsfont header files (for OpenBSD and NetBSD) are generated.
Regenerate dos/spleen.com after copyright bump to 2024.
Bump copyright year to 2024.
Spleen 2.0.2 release.
Update ChangeLog prior to the 2.0.2 release.
Update README to add a link to the Alpine Linux package.
Bump last updated dates in the 16x32 and 32x64 versions.

Merge pull request #35 from iucoen/master

Fix MALE and FEMALE character ordering in the 16x32 and 32x64 versions.

commit.message: MALE and FEMALE signs were swapped in 16x32 and 32x64
Spleen 2.0.1 release.
Update modification dates in the 8x16, 16x32, and 32x64 versions.
Update ChangeLog prior to the 2.0.0 release.

Remove C0 control characters range in the 8x16, 16x32, and 32x64 versions.

Only the copies in the range 00-1F have been deleted, the characters are
still present in the font.

This created issues in xterm under certain circumstances.

Reported by OpenBSD user 'Nato'. Thanks!
Add a new FAQ file answering frequently asked questions about Spleen.
